description:
MatLab and python scripts for fluctuations of phosphorylation and morphology of RNA polymerase II clusters. 

  Requirements  

 N2v package should be installed. The installation guide can be found in  https://github.com/juglab/n2v  

  Analysis Procedure  


	 Download the required data in Nikon .nd2 format. You need all data from&nbsp;recruited RNA polymerase II Serine 5 (Pol II Ser5P&nbsp;) and RNA polymerase II Serine 2 (Pol II Ser2P&nbsp;) in live sphere stage zebrafish embryos, visualized with antibody fragments (Fab). Images should be placed in a folder named &ldquo;image&rdquo;.&nbsp; 
	 Train the n2v network on a single image which is recorded with the same configuration as the live images. You can run the python script&nbsp;on Google Colab to save time and process resources. The script can be found at&nbsp;https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1KLJcvng36JiPlGH2GWaO2VxR2bppJ0xc?usp=sharing.&nbsp;The patches which are given to the network are of size (16, 64, 64), while 4/5&nbsp;of the patches were used to train the network and 1/5&nbsp;of all patches were used for the validation. You would better leave the network to be trained on each image at least for 70&nbsp;epochs with the neighbourhood radius = 10. You can also use the original script provided at&nbsp;https://github.com/juglab/n2v/blob/master/examples/3D/01_training.ipynb with this configuration.&nbsp; 
	 Python script  TimeLapsReconstruction.py  reads a single .nd2 image and reconstruct the ser5P images by n2v network. An already-trained network configuration is in  &quot;model.zip&quot; . You can easily replace it with your own n2v&nbsp;model.  TimeLapsReconstruction.py  put all the reconstructed ser5P images and the original ser2P images together and generate a single TIF file.&nbsp; If you would like to skip the previous steps and directly go to step 3 you can download the  EmbryoC_50ms_042_reconstructed.tif  and place it in the folder named &quot;image&quot;.&nbsp; 
	 Matlab script  morphology_fluctuation_analysis.m  reads the TIF file generated in the previous step and segments Pol II clusters and tracks clusters over time. For each focus mean intensity of Ser5P, the mean intensity of Ser2P, solidity and elongation is calculated and tracked over time. It shows how these quantifications change over time. The script later calculates the cross-correlation analysis of the temporal coordination of Pol II Ser5P intensity, Pol II Ser2P intensity, and solidity with elongation. Comments are provided n the script and the code is easily understandable. There are some functions that are called through  morphology_fluctuation_analysis.m  script. The required functions are in a folder named &ldquo;required function&rdquo;. You should download and unzip the folder and add it to your Matlab.

